race.comment: CALADAN (6) is a progressive gelding for the sharp R & C Jolly stable. Just missed here fresh but is sure to be better with that run under his belt. Is the one to beat. ARABELLA STAR (11) made a mess of her rivals at the latest, when clearly a class above. Only needs to hold her form to give this a shake but will likely get a long way back from the draw. Watch for her launching late. BRISTLER (4) has returned to career-best form and is sure to give himself every chance again in front. Will take some catching if left alone. PANTOJA (8) is a promising type returning and making his stable debut for the Hickmott camp. Readied with a pair of jumpouts and gets in super light with the 3kg claim. May need the run off 282 days but is definitely worth some thought. DAISYDOO (7) was good here fresh when missing by a long neck. Tougher this time but relishes this trip and is worth including.
